The '''Low Countries derby''' ({{lang-nl|Derby der Lage Landen}}), is the name given in [[Association football|football]] to any match between the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian]] and [[Netherlands national football team|Dutch national football teams]]. The countries have a long-standing tradition of rivalry in football, having played over 125 official Derbies so far.{{efn-ua|as of 2014}} Only [[Austria–Hungary football rivalry|Austria–Hungary]] and [[Argentina–Uruguay football rivalry|Argentina–Uruguay]] have been contested more often.<ref name="DerbyBelNed" >{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/belnedres.html|title=The "Derby der Lage Landen" |publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |first=Karel|last=Stokkermans |date=6 Mar 2014 |accessdate=16 May 2014}}</ref> Not only have the Low Countries met 18 times in the framework of major tournaments, they have also played at least [[#Belgium vs. Netherlands Cups|35 friendly cup duels]].<ref name="eu-footMR">{{cite web |title=Belgium national football team match results |publisher=eu-football.info |accessdate=5 Sep 2013 |url=http://eu-football.info/_matches.php?id=21 }}</ref>

